f(x) = \sum_{n=0}^\infty a_n(x-c)^n\text{ and }F(x)=\sum_{n=0}^\infty \frac{a_n}{n+1}(x-c)^{n+1}\\ \text{Then, we need }\int f(x)dx=\sum_{n=0}^\infty a_n\int(x-c)^ndx=\sum^\infty_{n=0}\dfrac{(x-c)^{n+1}}{n+1}=F(x)
